commit.message:
Try alternative way to set event mask

Certain implementation may have race miss the chance to setup the event
mask. Here we try to introduce two more ways to set event mask.

1. no trigger key -> set im event mask. This will be default to ic event
   mask if nothing is received. All modern im will forward all keys
   without using trigger key, which makes im event mask a good default
   fallback. _XimProcIMSetEventMask in libx11 will be called.
2. set event mask on focus in. This is an alternative place that makes
   sense to do so.

Either method seems work fine with kodi issue in fcitx/fcitx5#923

commit.message:
Make window property name used by XIM rotate and handle the possible issue with Xlib

Xlib rotation is cycle 20, which means if client sending event too fast,
the get property may not delete the property at all. We need to read all
the bytes to ensure all the data are read.

Also, use a large cycle number as our send buffer, since Xlib itself
does not use the same hack like us. Also our old way does not handle it
will as it may grow infinitely with number of events.
